  "response": "Here are several strategies for a middle-class Indian student to afford MS in USA:\n\n1. Financial Aid Options\n- University assistantships\n- Research/Teaching assistantships\n- Graduate scholarships\n- Merit-based fellowships\n- Need-based financial aid\n\n2. Funding Sources\n- Education loans from Indian banks\n- Education loans with lower interest rates\n- Loans with moratorium period\n- Collateral-free education loans\n- Government scholarship programs\n\n3. Cost-Reduction Strategies\n- Apply to universities offering more financial aid\n- Choose public/state universities\n- Consider universities in less expensive cities\n- Opt for universities with lower tuition fees\n- Apply for multiple scholarships simultaneously\n\n4. Work Opportunities\n- On-campus part-time jobs\n- Graduate assistantships\n- Optional Practical Training (OPT)\n- Curricular Practical Training (CPT)\n- internships during studies\n\n5. Additional Approaches\n- Start saving early\n- Maintain excellent academic profile\n- Develop strong research/technical skills\n- Learn programming/specialized skills\n- Build competitive profile for scholarships\n\n6. Alternative Funding\n- Family support\n- Personal savings\n- Education crowdfunding platforms\n- External scholarship competitions\n\nCareful planning and strategic approach can help manage financial challenges.",
